                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Daniel, a pawn<lb></lb>broker in Bowling-street. On the evening of the 20th of January, the prisoner brought this bed and wanted 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on it—I lent 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and he took out a hat and pair of gaiter which he had pledged for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he gave his name John Bridgen, 6, Devonshire-mews South—I might have mistaken his name—it might be George.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
